This product includes software developed at SlanchaAi, Inc.
(https://slancha.ai).

This product bundles model weights and assets:
- mmBERT-small INT8 (Apache 2.0). See the model card at
  https://huggingface.co/jhu-clsp/mmBERT-small.
- slancha-classifier-v1 (Apache 2.0). The 6 treelite heads + route
  selector + LMArena-derived ranking snapshot. Released under Apache
  2.0 by SlanchaAi.

Public LMArena leaderboard data (lmarena.ai) is incorporated by
reference for routing decisions.

The training-pipeline architecture in src/slancha_local/train/ takes
inspiration from the TensorZero project (https://github.com/tensorzero/tensorzero,
Apache 2.0): declarative TOML config of routes/variants, pluggable
training providers (local axolotl + remote HTTP), and the two-tier
(heuristic + LLM-judge pairwise) evaluation pattern. No code is copied;
the design patterns are.
